text.tspan: Agriculture value added per worker vs. GDP per capita, 1991 to 2017
Agriculture value added per worker versus gross domestic product (GDP) per capita, both measured in constant
2010 US$. Agriculture value added per worker is a measure of agricultural productivity. It corresponds to the ratio
between value added in agriculture (constant 2010 US$) and number of people employed in agriculture.
